trans-unit.source: Represents a word or short phrase that can be recognized.
trans-unit.target: Representerer et ord eller kort uttrykk som kan gjenkjennes.

trans-unit.source: Using the members of the SrgsToken class, you can specify three forms of a word: the <xref:System.Speech.Recognition.SrgsGrammar.SrgsToken.Display%2A> form, the <xref:System.Speech.Recognition.SrgsGrammar.SrgsToken.Text%2A> form, and a custom <xref:System.Speech.Recognition.SrgsGrammar.SrgsToken.Pronunciation%2A> for the word.
trans-unit.target: Ved hjelp av medlemmer av klassen SrgsToken, kan du angi tre former for et ord: den <xref:System.Speech.Recognition.SrgsGrammar.SrgsToken.Display%2A>skjemaet den <xref:System.Speech.Recognition.SrgsGrammar.SrgsToken.Text%2A>skjema og en egendefinert <xref:System.Speech.Recognition.SrgsGrammar.SrgsToken.Pronunciation%2A>for ordet.</xref:System.Speech.Recognition.SrgsGrammar.SrgsToken.Pronunciation%2A> </xref:System.Speech.Recognition.SrgsGrammar.SrgsToken.Text%2A> </xref:System.Speech.Recognition.SrgsGrammar.SrgsToken.Display%2A>

trans-unit.source: If multiple words are stored in a single SrgsToken object, each is treated as a different token internally and in the result.
trans-unit.target: Hvis flere ord er lagret i ett enkelt SrgsToken-objekt, behandles hver som et annet internt og i resultatet.

trans-unit.source: This class represents the `token` element defined by the World Wide Web Consortium (W3C) [Speech Recognition Grammar Specification (SRGS) Version 1.0.](http://go.microsoft.com/fwlink/?LinkId=201761).
trans-unit.target: Denne klassen representerer den `token` elementet definert av World Wide Web Consortium (W3C) [tale Recognition grammatikk spesifikasjonen (SRGS) versjon 1.0.](http://go.microsoft.com/fwlink/?LinkId=201761).

trans-unit.source: For information about the SRGS `token` element and details about its support by System.Speech, see [token Element](http://msdn.microsoft.com/en-us/3a9e8d64-7bd4-4188-a6f4-dbf28ea71632).
trans-unit.target: For informasjon om SRGS `token` elementet og detaljer om støtten av System.Speech, kan du se [token elementet](http://msdn.microsoft.com/en-us/3a9e8d64-7bd4-4188-a6f4-dbf28ea71632).

trans-unit.source: Initializes a new instance of the <xref href="System.Speech.Recognition.SrgsGrammar.SrgsToken"></xref> class and specifies the text to be recognized.
trans-unit.target: Initialiserer en ny forekomst av den <xref href="System.Speech.Recognition.SrgsGrammar.SrgsToken"> </xref> klasse og angir teksten som skal gjenkjennes.

trans-unit.source: Creates a <xref:System.Speech.Recognition.SrgsGrammar.SrgsToken> object whose <xref:System.Speech.Recognition.SrgsGrammar.SrgsToken.Text%2A> property is set initially to the value of the `text` parameter.
trans-unit.target: Oppretter en <xref:System.Speech.Recognition.SrgsGrammar.SrgsToken>objekt med <xref:System.Speech.Recognition.SrgsGrammar.SrgsToken.Text%2A>settes i utgangspunktet til verdien for den `text` parameteren.</xref:System.Speech.Recognition.SrgsGrammar.SrgsToken.Text%2A> </xref:System.Speech.Recognition.SrgsGrammar.SrgsToken>

trans-unit.source: The text of the new <xref href="System.Speech.Recognition.SrgsGrammar.SrgsToken"></xref> class instance.
trans-unit.target: Teksten for det nye <xref href="System.Speech.Recognition.SrgsGrammar.SrgsToken"> </xref> klasseforekomsten.

trans-unit.source: text is .
trans-unit.target: textis .

trans-unit.source: text is empty.
trans-unit.target: texter tom.

trans-unit.source: Gets or sets the display form of the text to be spoken.
trans-unit.target: Henter eller angir teksten som skal være talte Vis formatet.

trans-unit.source: Although they typically represent the same value, the Display form may be different than the <xref:System.Speech.Recognition.SrgsGrammar.SrgsToken.Text%2A> form for a word or phrase in a <xref:System.Speech.Recognition.SrgsGrammar.SrgsToken>.
trans-unit.target: Selv om de utgjør vanligvis samme verdi, kan vise-skjemaet være forskjellig fra <xref:System.Speech.Recognition.SrgsGrammar.SrgsToken.Text%2A>skjemaet for et ord eller uttrykk i en <xref:System.Speech.Recognition.SrgsGrammar.SrgsToken>.</xref:System.Speech.Recognition.SrgsGrammar.SrgsToken> </xref:System.Speech.Recognition.SrgsGrammar.SrgsToken.Text%2A>

trans-unit.source: For example, the display form may be an acronym, such as “USA”, while the text that will be spoken, and to which the <xref:System.Speech.Recognition.SrgsGrammar.SrgsToken.Pronunciation%2A> applies, is “United States of America”.
trans-unit.target: Visningsskjema kan for eksempel være en koden, for eksempel "USA" under teksten som skal være talte, og som den <xref:System.Speech.Recognition.SrgsGrammar.SrgsToken.Pronunciation%2A>gjelder, er "USA".</xref:System.Speech.Recognition.SrgsGrammar.SrgsToken.Pronunciation%2A>

trans-unit.source: A representation of the token as it should be displayed.
trans-unit.target: En representasjon av token som den skal vises.

trans-unit.source: An attempt is made to set Display to <xref uid="langword_csharp_null" name="null" href=""></xref>.
trans-unit.target: Er gjort forsøk på å vise WantDestinationQueue <xref uid="langword_csharp_null" name="null" href=""> </xref>.

trans-unit.source: An attempt is made to assign an empty string to Display.
trans-unit.target: Er gjort forsøk på å tilordne en tom streng skal vises.

trans-unit.source: Gets or sets the string that defines the pronunciation for the token.
trans-unit.target: Henter eller angir strengen som definerer uttalen for tokenet.

trans-unit.source: Phones are letters or symbols that describe the sounds of speech.
trans-unit.target: Telefoner er bokstaver eller symboler som beskriver lyd tale.

trans-unit.source: System.Speech supports three phonetic alphabets for specifying custom pronunciations: the Universal Phone Set (UPS), the Speech API (SAPI) Phone set, and the International Phonetic Alphabet (IPA).
trans-unit.target: System.Speech støtter tre phonetic bokstaver for å angi egendefinerte uttaler: Universal telefon angitt (UPSEN), tale-API (SAPI) telefon sett og internasjonal alfabetet (IPA).

trans-unit.source: The phones specified in Pronunciation must match the phonetic alphabet specified in <xref:System.Speech.Recognition.SrgsGrammar.SrgsDocument.PhoneticAlphabet%2A>.
trans-unit.target: Telefoner som er angitt i uttale må samsvare med alfabetet angitt i <xref:System.Speech.Recognition.SrgsGrammar.SrgsDocument.PhoneticAlphabet%2A>.</xref:System.Speech.Recognition.SrgsGrammar.SrgsDocument.PhoneticAlphabet%2A>

trans-unit.source: See [Lexicons and Phonetic Alphabets](http://msdn.microsoft.com/en-us/435e3c6f-6834-4e5a-b0f6-c17b2275dc51) for more information.
trans-unit.target: Se [Lexicons og Phonetic bokstaver](http://msdn.microsoft.com/en-us/435e3c6f-6834-4e5a-b0f6-c17b2275dc51) for mer informasjon.

trans-unit.source: The phones specified in Pronunciation indicate how the contents of <xref:System.Speech.Recognition.SrgsGrammar.SrgsToken.Text%2A> should be pronounced for successful recognition.
trans-unit.target: Telefoner som er angitt i uttale viser hvordan innholdet i <xref:System.Speech.Recognition.SrgsGrammar.SrgsToken.Text%2A>skal uttales for vellykket recognition.</xref:System.Speech.Recognition.SrgsGrammar.SrgsToken.Text%2A>

trans-unit.source: The speech recognition engine uses the pronunciation specified in Pronunciation to match speech input and returns the string contained by <xref:System.Speech.Recognition.SrgsGrammar.SrgsToken.Text%2A> in the recognition result.
trans-unit.target: Motor for talegjenkjenning bruker uttale som er angitt i uttale som samsvarer med tale inndataene og returnerer en streng som inneholder <xref:System.Speech.Recognition.SrgsGrammar.SrgsToken.Text%2A>i resultatet recognition.</xref:System.Speech.Recognition.SrgsGrammar.SrgsToken.Text%2A>

trans-unit.source: If the phones are not space-delimited or the specified string contains an unrecognized phone, the recognition engine does not recognize the specified pronunciation as a valid pronunciation of the word contained by <xref:System.Speech.Recognition.SrgsGrammar.SrgsToken.Text%2A>.
trans-unit.target: Hvis telefonene ikke mellomrom eller den angitte strengen inneholder en ukjent telefon, gjenkjenner ikke recognition motoren angitte uttalen som en gyldig Uttale av ordet finnes i <xref:System.Speech.Recognition.SrgsGrammar.SrgsToken.Text%2A>.</xref:System.Speech.Recognition.SrgsGrammar.SrgsToken.Text%2A>

trans-unit.source: Pronunciations specified in Pronunciation take precedence over pronunciations specified in lexicons associated with a grammar or a recognition engine.
trans-unit.target: Uttaler som er angitt i uttale overstyrer uttaler som er angitt i lexicons som er knyttet til en grammatikk eller en recognition-motor.

trans-unit.source: Also, the pronunciation in the Pronunciation property applies only to the single occurrence of the word or phrase contained by <xref:System.Speech.Recognition.SrgsGrammar.SrgsToken.Text%2A>.
trans-unit.target: Også gjelder uttalen i egenskapen uttale bare for en enkelt forekomst av den ord eller uttrykk som <xref:System.Speech.Recognition.SrgsGrammar.SrgsToken.Text%2A>.</xref:System.Speech.Recognition.SrgsGrammar.SrgsToken.Text%2A> inneholder

trans-unit.source: Returns a string containing phones from the phonetic alphabet specified in <xref:System.Speech.Recognition.SrgsGrammar.SrgsDocument.PhoneticAlphabet*>.
trans-unit.target: Returnerer en streng som inneholder telefoner fra alfabetet angitt i <xref:System.Speech.Recognition.SrgsGrammar.SrgsDocument.PhoneticAlphabet*>.</xref:System.Speech.Recognition.SrgsGrammar.SrgsDocument.PhoneticAlphabet*>

trans-unit.target: Er gjort forsøk på å angi uttale <xref uid="langword_csharp_null" name="null" href=""> </xref>.

trans-unit.source: An attempt is made to assign an empty string to Pronunciation.
trans-unit.target: Er gjort forsøk på å tilordne en tom streng til uttale.

trans-unit.source: Gets or sets the written form of the word that should be spoken.
trans-unit.target: Henter eller angir ord som skal være talte skriftlig formatet.

trans-unit.source: Although they typically represent the same value, the Text form may be different than the <xref:System.Speech.Recognition.SrgsGrammar.SrgsToken.Display%2A> form for a word or phrase in a <xref:System.Speech.Recognition.SrgsGrammar.SrgsToken>.
trans-unit.target: Selv om de utgjør vanligvis samme verdi, kan tekst-skjemaet være forskjellig fra <xref:System.Speech.Recognition.SrgsGrammar.SrgsToken.Display%2A>skjemaet for et ord eller uttrykk i en <xref:System.Speech.Recognition.SrgsGrammar.SrgsToken>.</xref:System.Speech.Recognition.SrgsGrammar.SrgsToken> </xref:System.Speech.Recognition.SrgsGrammar.SrgsToken.Display%2A>

trans-unit.source: For example, the <xref:System.Speech.Recognition.SrgsGrammar.SrgsToken.Display%2A> form may be an acronym, such as “USA”, while the text that will be spoken, and to which the <xref:System.Speech.Recognition.SrgsGrammar.SrgsToken.Pronunciation%2A> applies, is “United States of America”.
trans-unit.target: For eksempel den <xref:System.Speech.Recognition.SrgsGrammar.SrgsToken.Display%2A>skjemaet kan være en koden, for eksempel "USA" under teksten som skal være talte, og som den <xref:System.Speech.Recognition.SrgsGrammar.SrgsToken.Pronunciation%2A>gjelder, er "USA".</xref:System.Speech.Recognition.SrgsGrammar.SrgsToken.Pronunciation%2A> </xref:System.Speech.Recognition.SrgsGrammar.SrgsToken.Display%2A>

trans-unit.source: The default value for the Text property is an empty string—"".
trans-unit.target: Standardverdien for Text-egenskapen er en tom streng, "".
